Eco Research Bounty A:

Reward: 100-500+ points if accepted, depending on quality 
Issued: April 2nd, 2021 
Deadline: April 21st 2021, 11:59 PM Pacific Standard Time. 
Description: Document in detail the state of the economy where you live. What businesses are open, and how are they doing? What sorts of jobs do people do? What is produced? Do they commute somewhere, do they work remotely, or do they work near where they live? What has to be imported? What is exported? Detailed reports will be rewarded.

Hi @KingSuper, good question. Mainly, the thing that we're looking for is an understanding of how a given community's economy works that would normally be abstracted away by official statistics. What are the things that you can learn about only if you're on the ground in a village or a neighborhood, rather than being a guy back in the capital looking at some bureaucrat's report?
@nikkilikeonlynikki & @borand88, looking forward to reading these, but keep the above in mind. We might be able to learn more from focusing on a single neighborhood than a whole state.

Hi, guys! I am not  an expert here and yet I still have to add more details to my work. But below are some question that might help you. Just answer them and explain a bit more. Don't worry about your English, most of us here are not native speakers. Just write what you think is right. I can also help, just dm me. Let us give them what they want for ECO:eco_smile: :eco_love_you:                                                                                             
                                                                                                                                              
 Questions:
*Where do you live? It could be a city/town/neighborhood/village. Give a short detail about it. How does it look like?
*Write something about the people in your place.
*What is your place known for? What product/s your place make or service/s it offer? 
*What kind of businesses do you have in your place? Are they open now? Do they make profit? Are they happy/okay? if not, what are their problems? What is good and what is bad?
*What do the people in your area do to make money? 
*Where do they work? is their workplace inside your town or outside? 
*How do people go to work? Do they bike/walk? Do they ride a bus/train? Do they ride a taxi? Explain a little.
*What are the things you/your place buy from other country/ies?
*What are the things you/your place sell to other country/ies?
*What do you think are the improvements your place needs?

Bryce did not mention this, this is optional.
Additional questions with regards to Eco:
www.eco.com (you might want to read first to have a better understanding of ECO)
*If Eco will be in your area, will it be good? Why?
*How would the people in your area react with Eco? Will they like it? Why?
*If there is, what could be the issues/problems with Eco?

Lastly
*Read what you made and give your thoughts/feelings/opinion.
* You can also add photos to make it more and interesting
